1
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:10,850
我要你宣布  罗杰  我们好派他们去
I want a Declaration, Roger. So we can send them in.

2
00:00:10,890 --> 00:00:11,970
但总统女士
But, Madam President--

3
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:14,070
国民警卫队  联邦紧急事务管理署和环保署
I have the Guard, FEMA and the EPA

4
00:00:14,070 --> 00:00:16,850
都调动好了  就在城外等着
mobilized and waiting on the outskirts of that town.

5
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:18,640
我刚跟精炼厂联系过
I just got off the phone with the refinery.

6
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:20,920
泄露已经要烧尽了
The leak is well on its way to burning off.

7
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:24,970
据我所知  空气质量达到了危险程度
My understanding is that the air quality is dangerous.

8
00:00:24,970 --> 00:00:27,150
污染的确加重了  是的
The levels are somewhat elevated, yes,

9
00:00:27,150 --> 00:00:30,120
-但风向对我们有利  -但也可能变化
- but the winds are in our favor. - And subject to change.

10
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:31,660
风就是如此
That's how wind works.

11
00:00:31,830 --> 00:00:34,060
一两天内一切都会结束
This will all be over in a day or two,

12
00:00:34,060 --> 00:00:36,600
但要让民众撤离家园...
the idea of keeping these families out of their homes--

13
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,660
这谨慎的预防措施
This is a prudent precaution

14
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:41,170
我坐镇时  就希望采取这种措施
and on my watch, that's what I want to happen.

15
00:00:41,170 --> 00:00:43,760
我觉得不应该夸大情况
I don't think we should exaggerate the situation.

16
00:00:46,260 --> 00:00:49,170
你还记得选举当晚你的情况吗  州长
Do you remember where you were on election night, Governor?

17
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,470
我可记得
Because I do.

18
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:53,940
你本来要输了
You were going to lose.

19
00:00:54,920 --> 00:00:58,790
统计学上讲  你是根本不该赢的
Statistically, there is no reason you should have won.

20
00:01:02,420 --> 00:01:03,840
你考虑的时候
Keep the phone away from your mouth

21
00:01:03,850 --> 00:01:04,790
别把电话靠在嘴边  州长
while you're thinking, Governor.

22
00:01:04,790 --> 00:01:06,280
我听得到你的喘气声
I can hear you breathing.

23
00:01:07,910 --> 00:01:08,670
是
Yes.

24
00:01:11,220 --> 00:01:14,990
我觉得我是有必要宣布进入紧急状态
I do believe I need to declare a state of emergency.

25
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,240
当然了  这是你的决定
Of course, it's your call.

26
00:01:20,170 --> 00:01:21,290
我向你保证
And I assure you,

27
00:01:21,290 --> 00:01:24,080
联邦政府会全力支持你
you will have the full support of the federal government.

28
00:01:26,830 --> 00:01:29,870
我曾对自己保证不会像他那样
I promised myself I wouldn't be like him.

29
00:01:30,350 --> 00:01:32,420
但那就是弗兰西斯的典型做法  是吧
That was textbook Francis, wasn't it?

30
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:37,130
但他像递盐罐一样把我交给了他们
But he handed me over to them like a shaker of salt

31
00:01:37,210 --> 00:01:38,650
现在  他们不肯放手了
and now they won't let go.

32
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:42,810
这是他们自作自受
This is a wound of their own making.

33
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:47,550
副总统先生
Mr. Vice President?

34
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:51,890
请进
Yeah, come in.

35
00:01:55,660 --> 00:01:56,980
需要我等您一会儿吗  先生
Do you need a moment, sir?

36
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:59,110
不用
No, no.

37
00:02:00,010 --> 00:02:00,720
怎么了
What is it?

38
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:06,580
好
Okay.

39
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:11,400
州长
Governor?

40
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:19,970
{\an8}{\pos(98.3,102.65)}翻译   草草

41
00:02:20,510 --> 00:02:21,970
{\an8}{\pos(286.9,88.95)}时间轴   想念Gallifrey的wholock

42
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,010
{\an8}{\pos(92.4,242.45)}后期   饿得慌

43
00:02:24,980 --> 00:02:26,390
{\an8}{\pos(110.3,100.1)}校对  草草

44
00:02:26,730 --> 00:02:28,180
{\an8}{\pos(285.8,241.9)}顾问  老杜

45
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,820
{\an8}{\pos(100.4,98)}总监  草草

46
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:35,020
