仅供交流学习  禁止商用盈利

48
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:41,050
{\pos(196,180)}纸牌屋

49
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:41,050
{\an2}{\pos(208.1,242.25)}第六季  第二集

50
00:03:48,870 --> 00:03:50,070
他们说没事的
They said it was fine.

51
00:03:50,650 --> 00:03:54,530
就是一股烂鸡蛋和垃圾的味儿
It smelled like rotten eggs and trash. That's all.

52
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:56,410
水龙头里都是这个味儿
You could smell it coming out of the faucet.

53
00:03:56,900 --> 00:04:00,290
然后我儿子  他开始流鼻血了  我就想
And then my son, his-- his nose started to bleed and I thought,

54
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:02,450
-"跟这有关吗"  -你儿子现在在哪呢
- "Is that related?" - Where is your little boy right now?

55
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:05,400
现在吗  他跟他妈在做验伤
Now? He's in triage with his mom.

56
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:09,280
-那小家伙是我的心肝  -我知道
- He's my heart, that little guy. - No, I know. I know.

57
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,630
但女士  我可以问问吗
But, ma'am. If I may. You--

58
00:04:11,670 --> 00:04:13,840
您得告诉我们  这是不是真的
You have to tell us. Is this real or not?

59
00:04:13,850 --> 00:04:16,840
因为  起初他们说我们不需要撤离
Because at first they said that we don't need to evacuate,

60
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,070
但突然又改口说得撤离
and then all of a sudden that we should.

61
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:20,290
我要告诉你  一切都会没事的
I want you to know everything is going to be all right.

62
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:20,950
我保证
I promise you.

63
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:23,440
我们指望着那工厂通知我们情况呢
We were relying on that plant to keep us informed.

64
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:25,400
先生  你和你的安全
Sir, you and your safety

65
00:04:26,090 --> 00:04:27,680
才是最重要的
is the most important thing.

66
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:31,020
事实上  贝尔波特所有的家庭
In fact, all of the families of Bellport,

67
00:04:31,670 --> 00:04:33,130
才是唯一重要的
nothing else matters.

68
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:36,860
我要感谢奥姆斯泰德州长
I want to give my thanks to Governor Olmstead

69
00:04:36,990 --> 00:04:39,220
他今早快速果决地
for his quick and decisive act this morning

70
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:41,160
宣布了进入紧急状态
in declaring a state of emergency.

71
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,870
联邦紧急事务管理署  环保署
We have FEMA, we have EPA,

72
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:46,070
俄亥俄州国民警卫队
the Ohio National Guard.

73
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,410
都来了
They're all here.

74
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:51,700
没有人应该感到不安全
No one should ever feel unsafe.

75
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:53,740
...在她自己家里
In her own home.

76
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:57,300
你怎么会完全不知道呢  马克
And how is it you have no idea, Mark?

77
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:59,640
-这无所谓  -这很有所谓
- It doesn't matter. - Oh, it does matter.

78
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:01,980
这说明了我们的关系多靠不住
It speaks to this untenable arrangement.

79
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:04,650
我说了待会儿再说那个  先考虑回应
Later, I said. Let's stay focused on our response.

80
00:05:04,650 --> 00:05:06,420
她今早本都已经要签署法案了
She was all set to sign the bill this morning.

81
00:05:06,430 --> 00:05:08,370
我们叫了摄像师和记者什么的候着
We had photographers, a press pool waiting, the whole thing.

82
00:05:08,370 --> 00:05:11,310
-但她没签  是吧  -我这就过去
- But she didn't sign it, did she? - I'm on my way there now.

83
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:12,320
因为她在忙着
Because she was too busy

84
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,740
无中生有地制造紧急状况
manufacturing an emergency out of nothing.

85
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:17,510
别忘了是谁升级了事态  好吗
Look, let's not forget who escalated this. Okay?

86
00:05:17,510 --> 00:05:18,560
什么
Excuse me?

87
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,120
如果我们要合作  比尔
If we're working together, Bill,

88
00:05:20,330 --> 00:05:22,550
我需要参与每一个决定
I need to be included in every decision.

89
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:24,560
每一个
Every one.

90
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,220
我们没什么好谈的了
This conversation's over.

91
00:05:26,230 --> 00:05:28,050
老天爷啊
Oh, for God's sakes.

92
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:29,690
我会去贝尔波特跟安奈特碰头
I'll join Annette in Bellport.

93
00:05:29,690 --> 00:05:30,840
不  你别去
No, you won't.

94
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:33,170
你们中有一人到场就够糟了
One of you showing up on site is bad enough.

95
00:05:33,170 --> 00:05:34,570
安奈特  给我打电话
Annette, call me back.

96
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:37,380
马克
Mark.

97
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:39,500
马克  你还在吗
Mark, are you still there?

98
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:41,290
是的
Yes.

99
00:05:42,010 --> 00:05:44,330
让我跟他谈谈  我再打给你
Let me talk to him. I'll circle back.

100
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:58,830
大家好
Hello, everyone.

101
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:02,040
我是凯尔茜·斯图尔特
My name is Kelsey Stewart.

102
00:06:02,650 --> 00:06:04,400
代理新闻发言人
I'm the deputy press secretary,

103
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:06,690
今天我将为大家回答问题
and I will be taking your questions today.

104
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:08,370
莎拉
Sarah.

105
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,380
奥姆斯泰德州长是否真的
Is it true that Governor Olmstead

106
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:12,770
对宣布进入紧急状态很抗拒
was resistant to declaring a state of emergency?

107
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,510
州长的确宣布了进入紧急状态
The Governor did declare a state of emergency,

108
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,770
白宫也赞同了
and the White House concurs.

109
00:06:16,770 --> 00:06:18,820
工厂出了很大的问题
Something very wrong happened in that plant.

110
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:19,930
请说
Yes.

111
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,660
阿卡斯公司在泄露和爆炸事件方面
Arcas has been slow to provide any details

112
00:06:22,660 --> 00:06:24,670
迟迟不肯公布细节
when it comes to the leak and explosion.

113
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,750
更不用说两人在事故中丧生了
Not to mention the two lives lost in the accident.

114
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:28,680
他们跟白宫配合了吗
Have they been cooperating with the White House?

115
00:06:28,890 --> 00:06:30,550
现在总统去了第一线
Now that the president is on the ground,

116
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:33,260
他们似乎是更加愿意配合了
it seems that, yes, they have been more agreeable.

117
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,420
但这不是该问的问题
That's not the real question, though.

118
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:38,570
该有人问问
Somebody might want to ask,

119
00:06:38,570 --> 00:06:40,950
谢泼德无限责任公司怎么不出来说话
where is Shepherd Unlimited in all of this?

120
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:43,970
阿卡斯精炼厂是该家族集团的子公司
The Arcas Refinery is a subsidiary of the family's conglomerate.

121
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:45,880
你是说谢泼德家族
Are you saying that the Shepherds

122
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,660
清楚工厂的问题吗
are personally aware of problems at the plant?

123
00:06:48,850 --> 00:06:50,880
谁该负责  负怎样的责任
Who is responsible and how

124
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,450
这正是白宫和总统
is all the White House and the president

125
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:54,140
此刻想要查清的问题
are trying to find out at this point.

126
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:57,030
这会对总统
Will this have any effect

127
00:06:57,030 --> 00:06:59,200
准备签署的去监管法案有影响吗
on the regulatory bill on the president's desk?

128
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,440
总统不久后就会就此发表讲话
The president will be speaking on that shortly.

129
00:07:02,230 --> 00:07:02,950
马可斯
Marcus.

130
00:07:02,950 --> 00:07:06,260
总统在前总统死前
Was the president planning to divorce the former president

131
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:08,210
有打算与他离婚吗
in the days leading up to his death?

132
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:12,920
我们...
Let's...

133
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,610
-副总统先生  -大家早上好
- Mr. Vice President. - Morning, everyone.

134
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:18,550
希望斯图尔特小姐不会介意我回答几个问题
I hope Miss Stewart won't mind me taking a couple of questions.

135
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:21,970
副总统先生  请回答一个问题
Mr. Vice President, one question!

136
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:23,770
马可斯  你的消息源是谁
Marcus, who's your source?

137
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:26,750
-匿名官员  -不  这行不通了
- Unnamed officials. - Nope. We don't do that anymore.

138
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:28,530
我们要名字  你能说吗
We need names. You have a name?

139
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:31,170
说真的  你是哪听来的
I mean really, where do you get this?

140
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:33,130
前总统
The former president

141
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:35,500
生前的最后一晚
spent his last night alive

142
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:37,420
是在白宫他妻子身边度过的  就是这样
next to his wife in the White House. Period.

143
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,610
至于贝尔波特
As for Bellport...

144
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:41,780
知道全部事实之前  不要急着下结论
let's not jump to conclusions before all the facts are in.

145
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:42,700
还有什么
What else?

146
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,660
我们还在逐户查看  但这只是为防万一
We still going door to door, but it's really a precaution.

147
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:47,680
床位够吗
Are there enough beds?

148
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,300
我们有几间教堂地下室
We have a few church basements

149
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,960
如果有必要  还有当地监狱
and the local jail if we need more.

150
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:53,280
反正空气里还剩下的硫化氢
Whatever hydrogen sulfide there is left in the air

151
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:54,140
也要消散了
is already dissipating.

152
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:56,570
再过一两天  大家就能回自己的床上睡觉
In a day or two, people will be back sleeping in their own beds.

153
00:07:56,580 --> 00:07:57,880
您得明白
You have to understand,

154
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,560
总统女士
Madam President,

155
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:03,210
几乎所有人都会对化学品过度反应
most everyone overreacts when it comes to chemicals.

156
00:08:03,510 --> 00:08:05,220
我们有多年的经验
We have years of experience--

157
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:07,090
那死于事故的人呢
And the men who died in the accident?

158
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:10,530
那的确很悲惨  他们都是好员工
That's tragic, of course. They were valued employees.

159
00:08:10,530 --> 00:08:13,960
都是社区里的成员  他们不可替代
Members of the community. There's no way to replace them.

160
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,290
比尔·谢泼德呢
And Bill Shepherd?

161
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:18,160
-怎么  -他来过电话吗
- Yes. - Have you heard from him?

162
00:08:18,980 --> 00:08:22,390
我把情况通知了他和其他合伙人
I've kept him informed, as well as all of our partners.

163
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:23,860
比尔直接给我打过电话
Bill called me directly.

164
00:08:23,860 --> 00:08:25,640
他们准备采取一切必要措施
They're ready to do whatever's needed.

165
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,460
他们对贝尔波特非常重要
They're important to Bellport.

166
00:08:27,460 --> 00:08:28,730
他们建了当地的运动场
They built the local stadium.

167
00:08:28,740 --> 00:08:30,030
还有这个体育馆  他们出资...
Even this gymnasium. They contributed--

168
00:08:30,030 --> 00:08:32,240
我很清楚他们家族的慈善事业
No, I'm well aware of the family's philanthropy.

169
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,600
我问的不是那个
That wasn't the question.

170
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:37,680
是的  谢泼德先生一直在密切关注局势
Yes, Mr. Shepherd has been monitoring the situation closely.

171
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:39,460
我想在这一代巡视一圈
I would like to tour the area.

172
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:44,260
可以吗  州长
Is that a problem, Governor?

173
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,300
当然  据我所知没问题
No, no, not to my understanding.

174
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:50,740
我还想带您去
I was hoping to get you over to--

175
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:52,520
我们的验伤处
to where we set up our triage.

176
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,750
我们最好还是按日程来...
It might be best if we stick to the itinerary--

177
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:56,020
我想自己亲眼看看
I'd actually like to see it for myself.

178
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:58,420
当然  除非你们说不行
Unless, of course, you tell me otherwise.

179
00:08:58,790 --> 00:08:59,900
不  当然可以
No, of course not.

180
00:09:07,740 --> 00:09:11,670
警卫队标记了已撤离的房子
The guard marks the doors of the evacuees.

181
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:14,340
都是标准程序
Pretty standard procedure.

182
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,360
停车  我好像看到了人
Stop the car. I think I see someone.

183
00:09:20,090 --> 00:09:21,100
停车
Stop the car.

184
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:25,230
总统女士  我们会叫人再回来的
Madam President, we'll have someone circle back.

185
00:09:25,230 --> 00:09:26,470
马上停车
Stop the car now.

186
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:36,970
该死
Damn it.

187
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,350
她安全吗
Is she safe?

188
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:42,270
没有百分之百的安全
Nothing is 100% safe.

189
00:09:57,380 --> 00:09:59,040
有人吗  有人在吗
Hello. Anyone here?

190
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,330
那男孩差点瞎掉一只眼睛
The boy could have lost an eye.

191
00:10:25,330 --> 00:10:26,560
我们不能那么对待别人
That's not how we treat people.

192
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,260
她怎么能这么做
How could she?

193
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:28,440
天呐  伊丽莎白  行了
My God, Elizabeth, stop it.

194
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:30,130
我养的是个女儿还是野兽
Am I raising a daughter or an animal?

195
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:31,710
他们才是野兽  他们那么攻击她
They're the animals, the way they attacked her.

196
00:10:31,710 --> 00:10:34,420
好啊  替她说话吧你就
Oh, of course, take her side. Of course!

197
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:36,530
她也该了解这世界了
It's time she learned about the world.

198
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:40,390
漂亮姑娘要对她们的美貌负责
Pretty girls have a responsibility to their beauty.

199
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:43,190
肯定是她激了那些男孩
I'll bet she dared those boys.

200
00:10:43,590 --> 00:10:44,810
真丢脸
Shame on her.

201
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:48,880
你怎么就不能乖乖听话
Why can't you just do as you're told?

202
00:10:49,970 --> 00:10:51,200
是啊  为什么
Why, indeed?

203
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:54,180
总统女士  总统女士
Madam President! Madam President.

204
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:58,710
总统女士
Madam President...

205
00:11:00,490 --> 00:11:02,400
我们最好回去了
might be best if we head back.

206
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:04,890
房子安全吗
So, the house is safe?

207
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:14,720
那喝一口
Drink it then.

208
00:11:22,730 --> 00:11:23,840
我猜也是
I thought so.

209
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:45,960
{\an8}{\pos(230.4,252.4)}谢泼德自由基金会

210
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:48,970
-但我在答应什么  -我可以给你读一遍
- But what am I agreeing to? - I can read it for you.

211
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:49,930
我识字
I can read.

212
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:51,840
这是干什么的
And what's this for?

213
00:11:52,970 --> 00:11:54,570
这是让应用能分析出
That lets the app figure out

214
00:11:54,570 --> 00:11:56,140
我们怎样才能最好地施以帮助
how we can be most helpful.

215
00:11:56,140 --> 00:11:58,120
可以根据你的具体需求来制定计划
It can be tailored to your specific needs.

216
00:11:58,130 --> 00:11:59,550
我们想让你及时了解情况
We want to keep you informed.

217
00:11:59,570 --> 00:12:02,230
我们希望你在事发前就知道要发生什么
We want you to know what happens before it happens.

218
00:12:02,810 --> 00:12:04,330
这是不能靠政府的
You can't trust the government to do that.

219
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,480
你好  我是赛斯·格雷森
Hello, my name is Seth Grayson.

220
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,170
认识你很高兴
Nice to meet you.

221
00:12:07,170 --> 00:12:08,490
我是谢泼德自由基金会的
I'm with Shepherd Freedom Foundation,

222
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:09,960
可以跟你谈谈吗
can I talk to you for a second?

223
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:13,720
当然  我看了宣传册
Sure thing. I was looking at the pamphlet saying just...

224
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:12,980
{\an8}{\pos(257.4,231)}同意

225
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,070
是总统
It's the president.

226
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:47,860
总统女士
Madam President.

227
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:52,140
是谁的主意  把戒指放他床上
Whose idea was it? To leave it on his bed?

228
00:12:52,890 --> 00:12:53,960
别在这儿说
Not here.

229
00:12:55,970 --> 00:12:58,930
谢泼德自由基金会是来帮忙的
The Shepherd Freedom Foundation is here to help.

230
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:03,160
联邦政府将帮助你们
The federal government is here to help you.

231
00:13:03,730 --> 00:13:05,030
是啊  总统女士
Yes, Madam President.

232
00:13:05,350 --> 00:13:08,110
美国的问题要得到解决
The only way America's problems will be solved

233
00:13:08,110 --> 00:13:11,700
就得靠政府和私企联手
is through alliances between government and private industry,

234
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:13,250
各司其职
each doing its part.

235
00:13:15,780 --> 00:13:17,620
我跟三军统帅可是老交情了
The Commander in Chief and I go way back.

236
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:20,160
是啊  我知道谢泼德家族会
We do. And I know I have the full cooperation

237
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,650
完全配合我的工作
from the Shepherd family.

238
00:13:21,690 --> 00:13:24,290
阿卡斯这种公司
The blatant disregard for human life

239
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:25,860
对生命的公然漠视...
exhibited by companies like Arcas--

240
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:28,950
阿卡斯公司是一心想保护其员工的安全的
Arcas is committed to the safety of its workers.

241
00:13:28,950 --> 00:13:30,670
如果能得到助力
And with the help of...

242
00:13:31,430 --> 00:13:34,240
比如正确的立法  像是《未来法案》
the right kind of legislation, like the FUTURE Act.

243
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:36,500
此刻正在接受审核
Which is under review at the moment.

244
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:38,510
法案通过前
Until then,

245
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:42,430
我要让环保署的犯罪调查处
I am hereby moving the EPA's Criminal Investigative Division

246
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:52,360
{\pos(203.7,226.45)}总统亲临化学泄露事故现场

247
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:43,700
进驻五角大楼
into the Pentagon,

248
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:48,310
他们将拥有军队的力量和资源支持
where it will enjoy the forces and the resources of our military.

249
00:13:48,740 --> 00:13:51,080
他们会调查这起灾难的
And they will investigate this disaster.

250
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:53,550
我以我丈夫的坟墓起誓
I swear on my husband's grave,

251
00:13:53,550 --> 00:13:55,830
我一定会查明究竟发生了什么
I will find out what happened here.

252
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,580
谢谢您的支持
Thank you for your support.

253
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:03,390
我本想放在你床上呢
I wanted to leave it on your bed.

254
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,650
别犯傻  那对我没用
Don't be thick, thick I can't use.

255
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:12,780
她真提出离婚了吗
Did she actually ask for a divorce?

256
00:14:12,780 --> 00:14:13,790
那要紧吗
As if that matters.

257
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:15,850
如果我被要求给出这么问的凭据呢
And if I'm asked to justify the question?

258
00:14:15,850 --> 00:14:18,500
他们不正面回答  就是足够的凭据了
It was justified the moment they didn't have an answer.

259
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:20,790
总统最不希望
The last thing the president wants

260
00:14:20,790 --> 00:14:22,740
谈前总统的事了
is to be talking about the former president.

261
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:24,020
那我问问你
Let me ask you this.

262
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,300
总统甩开
How did your mother feel

263
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:27,640
你妈妈的手时  她是什么感觉
when the president yanked her hand away like that?

264
00:14:27,690 --> 00:14:29,930
那不关你的事  马可斯
That's none of your goddamn business, Marcus.

265
00:14:33,660 --> 00:14:43,660
{\an1}{\pos(138.9,225.7)}总统抽手了吗
安德伍德尴尬握手时刻在网上疯传

266
00:14:33,770 --> 00:14:35,340
-抽手  你是这么说的吗  -是啊
- Recoil? Is that the word you used? - Yeah,

267
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:36,200
我看就是这样
that's what I see.

268
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,040
-开玩笑吗  -不是
- Are you kidding me? - No.

269
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:38,350
我们真要浪费时间
Are we really gonna waste time

270
00:14:38,350 --> 00:14:40,410
剖析两个女人之间的一个手势吗
dissecting a gesture between two women?

271
00:14:40,410 --> 00:14:41,800
诺拉说得对  我当时在场
Nora's right. I was there.

272
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:42,940
没有什么抽手
There wasn't a recoil.

273
00:14:42,940 --> 00:14:43,950
我同意汤姆的话
I gotta agree with Tom here.

274
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:46,680
我觉得安奈特·谢泼德是想硬拉着总统
For me, it's Annette Shepherd sort of manhandling the president

275
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:49,390
摆出胜利姿态  然后我看到她惊了一下
as a sign of victory, and then I detect a flinch.

276
00:14:49,390 --> 00:14:51,700
就那么一下下  然后就抽了手
A slight flinch, then recoil.

277
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:54,010
-抽手...  -她是想切断自己
- Recoil? I mean-- - She's trying to separate herself

278
00:14:54,010 --> 00:14:57,100
跟原本计划的弗兰西斯·安德伍德基金会
from the primary source of the funding for what was to be

279
00:14:57,100 --> 00:15:00,180
-主资金源的关系  -这是关于过失
- the Francis J. Underwood Foundation. - This is about culpability.

280
00:15:00,180 --> 00:15:03,380
她是去贝尔波特要求责任方负责的
She went to Bellport to hold those responsible accountable.

281
00:15:03,390 --> 00:15:06,710
谢泼德无限责任公司这样的公司一直在被拖后腿
Companies like Shepherd Unlimited have been hamstrung.

282
00:15:06,710 --> 00:15:08,740
所以她要签署的法案才如此重要
And that's why this bill on her desk is so important.

283
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:11,780
如果不能执行  立法就毫无意义
Legislation means nothing without proper enforcement.

284
00:15:11,790 --> 00:15:14,220
给环保署武器只是固执
Weaponizing the EPA is wrongheaded.

285
00:15:14,230 --> 00:15:15,410
而且根本不能...
And it does nothing to make--

286
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:18,800
与其给她的每一个行为找负面动机
Instead of ascribing negative motives to her every action,

287
00:15:18,810 --> 00:15:21,030
我们为什么不能承认  安德伍德总统
why can't we just accept that President Underwood

288
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:23,170
去做了总统该做的事
was out there being presidential?

289
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:24,320
她让你
She put the fear of God

290
00:15:24,330 --> 00:15:26,480
和你的新朋友感到害怕了  格雷森先生
into you and your new friends, Mr. Grayson.

291
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:28,770
做总统该做的事  就该签署法案
Being "Presidential" means signing the bill

292
00:15:28,770 --> 00:15:31,080
更新陈旧的监管
and modernizing antiquated regulations.

293
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:32,230
你怎么会知道
As if you would know.

294
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:34,100
那是什么意思
What's that supposed to mean?

295
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:36,870
她丈夫  你曾是他政府的成员
Her husband, whose administration you were a part of,

296
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:37,370
本来就要...
was about to--

297
00:15:37,370 --> 00:15:40,420
正准备建立一个慈善基金会
Was in the midst of setting up a philanthropic foundation.

298
00:15:40,430 --> 00:15:42,220
她丈夫都要被起诉了
Her husband was about to be indicted.

299
00:15:42,220 --> 00:15:43,780
什么  八字没一撇的事
Excuse me, there wasn't even a grand jury.

300
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:45,130
我有可靠消息称
I have it on good authority

301
00:15:45,140 --> 00:15:48,100
他要被起诉了  而她要赦免他
he was about to be indicted, and she was about to pardon him.

302
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:49,970
但她还想离婚
But she also wanted a divorce.

303
00:15:49,970 --> 00:15:51,970
好挽救自己  撇清关系
To save herself. Distance herself.

304
00:15:51,970 --> 00:15:53,350
因为  拜托  难道你能说
Because, come on. Are you telling me

305
00:15:53,350 --> 00:15:55,760
她对他的作为一无所知吗
she knew nothing of what he was up to?

306
00:15:55,820 --> 00:15:58,030
-如果他有罪  她也有  -汤姆
- If he was guilty, she was guilty. - Tom? Tom,

307
00:15:58,030 --> 00:15:59,190
我十分尊敬你
I have great respect for you

308
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:00,720
还有你在《先驱报》的工作
and the work you've done at the Herald.

309
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:04,890
但你能就她自己的表现来评述她吗
But are you even capable of defining her on her own terms?

310
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,660
抱歉  前一秒她还是悲伤寡妇
I'm sorry. One minute she's playing the grieving widow

311
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:08,690
-下一秒  她又借题发挥  -正是
- and the next, she's riding on the coattails. - Case in point.

312
00:16:08,690 --> 00:16:11,090
虽然这么说很过分
This may be an unseemly thing to say,

313
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:13,270
但很可能
but it's quite possible

314
00:16:13,270 --> 00:16:16,250
她丈夫的死  是总统走了大运
her husband's death was the president's lucky day.

315
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,430
你在这里可以畅所欲言
You can say whatever you want in here.

316
00:16:20,430 --> 00:16:22,290
不管你有什么感觉  有什么想法
Whatever your feeling, thinking.

317
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:24,510
我质疑你的能力
I'm questioning your ability.

318
00:16:25,970 --> 00:16:27,170
我的能力
My ability?

319
00:16:28,330 --> 00:16:32,030
能不能分辨有道理的多疑和...
To tell the difference between justifiable paranoia and--

320
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:35,400
你还用那个词吗
Do you use the word anymore?

321
00:16:35,590 --> 00:16:36,380
"疯狂"
"Madness?"

322
00:16:38,550 --> 00:16:40,340
你对什么感到多疑
What do you feel paranoid about?

323
00:16:42,310 --> 00:16:43,570
我自己吧
Myself, maybe.

324
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:47,310
我们为什么做我们做的事  为谁而做
Why we do what we do and for who?

325
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:51,910
谁更邪恶  医生
Who's more evil, Doctor,

326
00:16:53,130 --> 00:16:55,550
发令者还是执行者
the taskmaster or the tasked?

327
00:16:55,890 --> 00:17:00,020
你觉得弗兰西斯·安德伍德背叛了你吗
Do you feel like Francis Underwood betrayed you?

328
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:02,510
我觉得我在想是谁背叛了他
I guess I'm wondering who betrayed him.

329
00:17:03,330 --> 00:17:04,430
你觉得呢
Who do you think?

330
00:17:05,050 --> 00:17:05,750
你吗
You?

331
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,410
我不知道我们的治疗是否还能帮我
I don't know if these sessions are helping me anymore.

332
00:17:16,980 --> 00:17:18,860
你为什么给我开药  医生
Why are you trying to drug me up, Doctor?

333
00:17:18,930 --> 00:17:20,910
我觉得你该考虑一下
I think you should consider it.

334
00:17:20,910 --> 00:17:21,980
氯氮平
Clozapine.

335
00:17:22,070 --> 00:17:24,050
你肯定知道那会把人变成什么样
You must know what that does to a person.

336
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:26,090
现在又有了新的抗精神病药物  道格
They're a newer class of antipsychotics, Doug.

337
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:27,300
副作用
The side effects

338
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:30,390
不像以前的那些那么严重了
are not as sensational as some of the older ones.

339
00:17:31,820 --> 00:17:33,950
你不非得这样受罪的
You don't have to suffer like this.

340
00:17:33,950 --> 00:17:35,220
据我所知
From my understanding,

341
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:37,340
光是副作用就能让你显得
the side effects themselves can make you look--

342
00:17:37,710 --> 00:17:41,310
我又得问  你是否还用"疯狂"这个词
And again, I'm asking you if you use this word "mad."

343
00:17:45,390 --> 00:17:46,800
你开玩笑吗
Are you fucking kidding me?

344
00:17:47,610 --> 00:17:48,290
什么
Pardon?

345
00:17:48,410 --> 00:17:49,770
你要一边看表
You're gonna talk to me about side effects

346
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:51,120
一边跟我聊副作用吗
while you look at your fucking clock?

347
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:53,150
不  你说得对  抱歉
No, you're right. I'm sorry.

348
00:17:53,150 --> 00:17:55,370
我们还是明天下午继续吧
We're gonna have to take this up tomorrow afternoon.

349
00:17:55,710 --> 00:17:58,010
这个话题要重大得多
This is a much bigger conversation.

350
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,850
不  我就现在说
No, I'm talking now.

351
00:18:06,130 --> 00:18:07,660
抱歉  但你的时间到了
I'm sorry, but your time is up.

352
00:18:07,660 --> 00:18:09,760
我才不在乎时间
I don't give a fuck about the time.

353
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:10,890
斯坦普先生
Mr. Stamper.

354
00:18:11,430 --> 00:18:12,790
我很高兴你终于决定
I'm glad that you finally decided

355
00:18:12,790 --> 00:18:14,630
好好利用你在这里的时间
to take advantage of your time here,

356
00:18:14,630 --> 00:18:15,860
但你清楚规矩
but you know the rules.

357
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:18,470
我哪都不去
I'm not going anywhere.

